00:00:08.840 --> 00:00:12.780
now, a panel on
citizenship on the move.

00:00:12.780 --> 00:00:18.050
And may I ask the panel
members to come up to the stage

00:00:18.050 --> 00:00:23.480
and take their seats while I
have the honor of introducing

00:00:23.480 --> 00:00:26.880
Professor Jacqueline Bhabha.

00:00:26.880 --> 00:00:29.310
Professor Jacqueline
Bhabha is the director

00:00:29.310 --> 00:00:33.540
of research at the Harvard FXB
Center for Health and Human

00:00:33.540 --> 00:00:36.810
Rights, a professor of
the practice of health

00:00:36.810 --> 00:00:39.690
and human rights at the
Harvard T.H. Chan School

00:00:39.690 --> 00:00:42.930
of Public Health, and
also an adjunct lecturer

00:00:42.930 --> 00:00:46.188
in public policy at the
Harvard Kennedy School.

00:00:46.188 --> 00:00:48.480
Before coming to Harvard,
she directed the Human Rights

00:00:48.480 --> 00:00:50.790
Program at the
University of Chicago

00:00:50.790 --> 00:00:53.280
