00:52:00.600 --> 00:52:01.890
and regulated.

00:52:01.890 --> 00:52:06.193
One of the few studies
that was done used--

00:52:06.193 --> 00:52:07.860
let me just make sure
I get this right--

00:52:07.860 --> 00:52:12.630
the American national
election survey data in 2016

00:52:12.630 --> 00:52:17.760
to look at what percentage
of the white population

00:52:17.760 --> 00:52:22.260
concurs with beliefs that are
in sync with white nationalism.

00:52:22.260 --> 00:52:25.020
And the researcher
that did this study

00:52:25.020 --> 00:52:27.450
looked at three core beliefs--

00:52:27.450 --> 00:52:29.130
a strong sense of
white identity,

00:52:29.130 --> 00:52:31.440
a belief in white
solidarity, and a feeling

00:52:31.440 --> 00:52:33.090
of white victimization--

00:52:33.090 --> 00:52:36.210
and determined that
based on this sample

00:52:36.210 --> 00:52:40.290
that approximately 6% of
the white population or 11

00:52:40.290 --> 00:52:44.160
million white people
agree with those three.

00:52:44.160 --> 00:52:48.900
However, if you take them
separately, about 30% to 40%

00:52:48.900 --> 00:52:51.660
of white people agree with
at least one of those.

00:52:51.660 --> 00:52:54.600
