00:56:51.840 --> 00:56:56.130
So for those of us who've
been in Greece since 2015,

00:56:56.130 --> 00:56:59.550
and also in Beirut, what
we have been witnessing

00:56:59.550 --> 00:57:03.540
is a tremendous amount
of refugee activism.

00:57:03.540 --> 00:57:06.690
And that comes, in part,
because of the need for people

00:57:06.690 --> 00:57:09.420
to be saving each other's lives.

00:57:09.420 --> 00:57:11.850
So I think, for
example, of people

00:57:11.850 --> 00:57:14.910
waiting in Izmir
in Turkey, wanting

00:57:14.910 --> 00:57:17.130
to come across on the rafts.

00:57:17.130 --> 00:57:20.640
And the smugglers are
not saying, excuse me,

00:57:20.640 --> 00:57:23.470
the only people on the
rafts can be Syrian.

00:57:23.470 --> 00:57:23.970
Right?

00:57:23.970 --> 00:57:25.350
So what that means
is that people

00:57:25.350 --> 00:57:28.890
are coming across and
fearing for their lives,

00:57:28.890 --> 00:57:33.350
creating solidarity with
each other in that moment.

00:57:33.350 --> 00:57:37.970
So Afghans and Kurds and
Palestinians and Syrians

00:57:37.970 --> 00:57:38.900
together.

00:57:38.900 --> 00:57:42.890
And then walking up the
mountain pass in Lesbos

00:57:42.890 --> 00:57:44.450
all the way to Mytelini.

00:57:44.450 --> 00:57:46.490
And what I was witnessing
over and over again

00:57:46.490 --> 00:57:50.830
is, any time an elder
needed to sit on a backpack,

00:57:50.830 --> 00:57:54.210
it didn't matter what
country that elder was from,

00:57:54.210 --> 00:57:56.900
especially if she was a woman,
she would get that backpack.

00:57:56.900 --> 00:57:59.630
And then you see now in
[INAUDIBLE] and in [INAUDIBLE]

00:57:59.630 --> 00:58:04.400
and in [INAUDIBLE]
organizing happening across

00:58:04.400 --> 00:58:07.260
so many ethnicities
and religion as well.

00:58:07.260 --> 00:58:10.670
So I want to lift that up
as, you know, coming back

00:58:10.670 --> 00:58:14.660
