nature of humanitarianism

00:59:15.830 --> 00:59:20.360
that was feeding
divisions, whereas what's

00:59:20.360 --> 00:59:22.850
happening in some of the
situations you were describing

00:59:22.850 --> 00:59:27.180
and also in other
parts of the world,

00:59:27.180 --> 00:59:30.760
including Jordan, is a
different type of solidarity.

00:59:30.760 --> 00:59:34.280
And a Sheikh said
to me in a workshop

00:59:34.280 --> 00:59:36.380
we were running in Jordan--

00:59:36.380 --> 00:59:38.450
we were running
workshops with people

00:59:38.450 --> 00:59:41.240
who were hosting refugees
and refugees themselves.

00:59:41.240 --> 00:59:42.920
Quite often, people
who are hosting

00:59:42.920 --> 00:59:45.740
refugees in Jordan and Lebanon
come from refugee families

00:59:45.740 --> 00:59:46.460
themselves.

00:59:46.460 --> 00:59:50.020
Largely Palestinian or another
kind of tradition or going way

00:59:50.020 --> 00:59:50.520
back.

00:59:50.520 --> 00:59:52.760
So there is a kind of
identification there.

00:59:52.760 --> 00:59:57.290
And the Sheikh said to me, we
don't have the word refugee

00:59:57.290 --> 00:59:57.920
here.

00:59:57.920 --> 00:59:58.670
That's yours.

00:59:58.670 --> 00:59:59.840
That's Western.

00:59:59.840 --> 01:00:02.220
We have guests and strangers.

01:00:02.220 --> 01:00:03.470
And technically, he's right.

01:00:03.470 --> 01:00:04.610
I mean, that's what
Michael Barnett

01:00:04.610 --> 01:00:06.485
was saying in the history
of humanitarianism.

01:00:06.485 --> 01:00:08.750
We invented this
category of refugee

01:00:08.750 --> 01:00:12.507
in order to administer those
people who were not citizens.

01:00:12.507 --> 01:00:14.090
They're actually
people who are moving

01:00:14.090 --> 01:00:16.887
for all sorts of reasons.

01:00:16.887 --> 01:00:18.470
And so one of the
things we need to do

01:00:18.470 --> 01:00:20.420
is invent a different
language for talking

01:00:20.420 --> 01:00:23.390
about hosting, guesting,
staying, staying

01:00:23.390 --> 01:00:24.140
too long maybe.

01:00:24.140 --> 01:00:26.070
Being an awkward
guest, whatever.

01:00:26.070 --> 01:00:27.410
It's never easy, we know.

01:00:27.410 --> 01:00:28.938
Many people [INAUDIBLE].

01:00:28.938 --> 01:00:30.980
But we desperately need
to find another language.

01:00:30.980 --> 01:00:32.022
And I think you're right.

