land, where we stand today.

01:01:33.090 --> 01:01:35.750
And why is that suggestive?

01:01:35.750 --> 01:01:40.520
Because if we would try to do
something serious about that,

01:01:40.520 --> 01:01:47.180
we'd have to dismantle all the
forms of property ownership,

01:01:47.180 --> 01:01:50.120
such as Harvard's
ownership of this land.

01:01:50.120 --> 01:01:52.550
At least there'd have
to be resolutions.

01:01:52.550 --> 01:01:58.610
Just as if we were going to
move beyond the nation state,

01:01:58.610 --> 01:02:02.180
we would have to
not only dismantle

01:02:02.180 --> 01:02:05.340
the building block for all
the world's organization,

01:02:05.340 --> 01:02:08.540
and certainly a
lot of democracies,

01:02:08.540 --> 01:02:10.700
and move to some other form.

01:02:10.700 --> 01:02:14.280
So I invite-- yes,
it's a bit startling,

01:02:14.280 --> 01:02:18.500
the notion of turning
back over to the Wampanoag

01:02:18.500 --> 01:02:22.100
where we're standing, but it
might jolt us out of ourselves

01:02:22.100 --> 01:02:25.820
to think of this problem
in very practical terms.

01:02:25.820 --> 01:02:28.400
How might we move beyond the
building block of the nation

01:02:28.400 --> 01:02:28.670
state?

