of blood purity.

01:02:46.590 --> 01:02:47.590
I'm not a scientist.

01:02:47.590 --> 01:02:49.770
But my question relates
to the relationship

01:02:49.770 --> 01:02:52.530
between a biological
conception of race

01:02:52.530 --> 01:02:55.560
and a social conception,
and whether--

01:02:55.560 --> 01:02:58.950
since now everyone can have
their genes sequenced--

01:02:58.950 --> 01:03:02.160
is it possible that white
nationalists might find out

01:03:02.160 --> 01:03:04.583
that they're related
to African-Americans

01:03:04.583 --> 01:03:06.000
and whether any
of that might have

01:03:06.000 --> 01:03:11.732
some consequences for these
political discussions?

01:03:11.732 --> 01:03:14.520
- Hannah.

01:03:14.520 --> 01:03:15.020
- Hello.

01:03:15.020 --> 01:03:16.160
My name is Hannah.

01:03:16.160 --> 01:03:19.040
I'm from the graduate school
of design here at Harvard.

01:03:19.040 --> 01:03:24.080
I only yesterday heard about
this term polypolitanism,

01:03:24.080 --> 01:03:30.170
which the professor used
instead of cosmopolitanism.

01:03:30.170 --> 01:03:33.140
It's an idea that we can
belong to many instead

01:03:33.140 --> 01:03:38.420
of either nation state or
international, so it to me

01:03:38.420 --> 01:03:39.620
was very hopeful.

01:03:39.620 --> 01:03:47.190
And it sounded very
realizable that we

01:03:47.190 --> 01:03:49.320
don't have to sort of
dismantle everything

01:03:49.320 --> 01:03:52.380
that we have in order to
go for another future.

01:03:52.380 --> 01:03:55.350
But we can actually have
more than one identity,

01:03:55.350 --> 01:03:57.180
and I resonate with that.

01:03:57.180 --> 01:03:59.730
And I think a lot of people
resonate with wanting

01:03:59.730 --> 01:04:06.630
to navigate as multiple
sort of people.

01:04:06.630 --> 01:04:07.130
So yeah.

01:04:07.130 --> 01:04:10.650
So I was wondering if
you had any thoughts

01:04:10.650 --> 01:04:14.640
on this idea of
polypolitanism and if you

01:04:14.640 --> 01:04:16.260
have any critiques of that.

01:04:16.260 --> 01:04:19.400
I'm just curious what
you thought of that.

01:04:19.400 --> 01:04:19.900
Thank you.

01:04:19.900 --> 01:04:22.950
- Thank you very much, indeed.

01:04:22.950 --> 01:04:25.507
So who'd like to start?

01:04:25.507 --> 01:04:26.590
Alex, why don't you start?

01:04:26.590 --> 01:04:29.310
- I can start.

01:04:29.310 --> 01:04:33.540
The question of ancestry
testing and white nationalism

01:04:33.540 --> 01:04:35.610
is a very interesting one.

01:04:35.610 --> 01:04:39.840
And what researchers
have found--

01:04:39.840 --> 01:04:42.540
and, you know, you
can learn about

01:04:42.540 --> 01:04:45.870
if you actually go into
some of these message boards

01:04:45.870 --> 01:04:50.130
where white nationalists or
focusing on ancestry testing

01:04:50.130 --> 01:04:52.230
is they like the
results of the test

01:04:52.230 --> 01:04:55.170
when they tell them
what they want to hear.

01:04:55.170 --> 01:04:57.300
But they actually don't rely--

01:04:57.300 --> 01:04:59.670
they like the idea of the tests.

01:04:59.670 --> 01:05:02.880
And that's in fact why the
American Society for Human

01:05:02.880 --> 01:05:05.700
Genetics recently made
a very strong statement

01:05:05.700 --> 01:05:08.520
against white supremacy
and the misuse

01:05:08.520 --> 01:05:12.930
of these tests, the
scientific distortion of them

01:05:12.930 --> 01:05:15.150
by white supremacists.

01:05:15.150 --> 01:05:17.220
They specifically
used that term.

01:05:17.220 --> 01:05:19.170
However, one of
the aspects that's

01:05:19.170 --> 01:05:21.600
very interesting about
white nationalists

01:05:21.600 --> 01:05:24.510
is, because they
don't they frequently

01:05:24.510 --> 01:05:28.500
don't get the results
they want, they

01:05:28.500 --> 01:05:32.340
engage in a romanticized
notion of community.

01:05:32.340 --> 01:05:36.000
They often ignore genetic tests.

01:05:36.000 --> 01:05:39.690
They partake of the
metaphors of blood and soil.

01:05:39.690 --> 01:05:42.300
But for example, if they
don't get a result they want,

01:05:42.300 --> 01:05:45.660
they'd say, well, I'm
white in spirit and soul.

01:05:45.660 --> 01:05:51.900
Or I feel a connection to the
medieval past or the Crusades.

01:05:51.900 --> 01:05:54.810
And there's a lot of
these fantasy invocations.

01:05:54.810 --> 01:05:58.080
So this is happening on
multiple discursive levels.

01:05:58.080 --> 01:06:03.300
But the ancestry testing
does kind of cross that,

01:06:03.300 --> 01:06:08.130
and that will continue to
play a role in certain aspects

01:06:08.130 --> 01:06:12.810
of at least claiming identity.

01:06:12.810 --> 01:06:14.750
- Thank you.

01:06:14.750 --> 01:06:19.060
Theresa, do you want to comment
on Harvard handing over--

01:06:19.060 --> 01:06:21.130
[LAUGHTER]

01:06:21.630 --> 01:06:24.040
- OK, good.

01:06:24.040 --> 01:06:25.310
I think-- where to start?

01:06:25.310 --> 01:06:26.977
One of the things we
talk about, there's

01:06:26.977 --> 01:06:30.430
a lot of debate about
doing land acknowledgments.

01:06:30.430 --> 01:06:33.250
And part of it is because
people don't want it just become

01:06:33.250 --> 01:06:35.380
like a rote one off thing.

01:06:35.380 --> 01:06:38.380
They want people to
sort of think like--

01:06:38.380 --> 01:06:39.830
it's not invisible anymore.

01:06:39.830 --> 01:06:41.140
It's not erased anymore.

01:06:41.140 --> 01:06:43.330
But to think about
this idea of, OK,

01:06:43.330 --> 01:06:47.080
what is the relationship that
comes with that acknowledgment?

01:06:47.080 --> 01:06:49.820
Because you're asking
this big question.

01:06:49.820 --> 01:06:50.890
How do we dismantle?

01:06:50.890 --> 01:06:53.710
You know, what is this
anti-colonial vision?

01:06:53.710 --> 01:06:55.840
It starts with
having relationships.

01:06:55.840 --> 01:06:59.920
And moving out of possession
to relationship, I think,

01:06:59.920 --> 01:07:03.760
is where it has to start.

01:07:03.760 --> 01:07:05.110
So acknowledging that.

01:07:05.110 --> 01:07:06.550
And then, OK,
where do we go now?

01:07:06.550 --> 01:07:08.380
What do we do to build
those relationships

01:07:08.380 --> 01:07:10.270
and to keep them
going and to have

01:07:10.270 --> 01:07:13.030
that be an ongoing process?

01:07:13.030 --> 01:07:16.270
In our earliest
treaties that we have

01:07:16.270 --> 01:07:18.410
between Haudenosaunee
people and the newcomers,

01:07:18.410 --> 01:07:21.010
they were treaties of
peace and friendship.

01:07:21.010 --> 01:07:22.540
And they were
treaties about ways

01:07:22.540 --> 01:07:28.280
to coexist and to have
independent political systems,

01:07:28.280 --> 01:07:30.580
but to exist in a
non-colonial relationship

01:07:30.580 --> 01:07:34.030
where there wasn't
imposition or interference.

01:07:34.030 --> 01:07:35.530
And so those visions
are out there.

01:07:35.530 --> 01:07:39.430
And they're principled on
these ideas of having relations

01:07:39.430 --> 01:07:43.180
in a different way that aren't
about necessarily possession,

01:07:43.180 --> 01:07:47.290
and can we think about
sort of structuring

01:07:47.290 --> 01:07:48.730
things more along those lines.

01:07:51.720 --> 01:07:52.220
- Yeah.

01:07:52.220 --> 01:07:54.800
No, but back to
the nation state.

01:07:54.800 --> 01:07:58.250
Because there's not one
type of nation state.

01:07:58.250 --> 01:08:01.110
It's always changing
and can change.

01:08:01.110 --> 01:08:04.700
I really was touched
by your translation

01:08:04.700 --> 01:08:07.250
of what nationality means.

01:08:07.250 --> 01:08:08.600
Bodies in the land.

01:08:08.600 --> 01:08:12.950
And I just thought that's really
powerful and that could work.

01:08:12.950 --> 01:08:15.225
And then it all kind of
looked back to this morning.

01:08:15.225 --> 01:08:16.850
And actually what we
have at the moment

01:08:16.850 --> 01:08:19.520
is a version of a nation
state which isn't actually

01:08:19.520 --> 01:08:24.140
about sharing and
solidarity, or just sharing,

01:08:24.140 --> 01:08:25.729
learning how to share.

01:08:25.729 --> 01:08:29.240
As the panel pointed out,
it's about power and money

01:08:29.240 --> 01:08:33.050
and a version of a fantasy
nation state, which is actually

01:08:33.050 --> 01:08:36.540
about keeping power and money
for certain types of people.

01:08:36.540 --> 01:08:39.104
So I wouldn't want to trash
the idea of the nation state

01:08:39.104 --> 01:08:41.479
because I don't think there's
just one idea of the nation

01:08:41.479 --> 01:08:41.979
state.

01:08:41.979 --> 01:08:44.270
They're always competing,
arguing about the best way

01:08:44.270 --> 01:08:45.450
to be together.

01:08:45.450 --> 01:08:48.620
But I do think-- and that's why
I love the bodies in the land--

01:08:48.620 --> 01:08:53.510
it's time to have more of an
upfront struggle about defining

01:08:53.510 --> 01:08:55.130
new definitions of
what it might mean

01:08:55.130 --> 01:08:58.460
to be in the nation or
different nations in one state.

01:08:58.460 --> 01:09:01.220
I mean bi-nationality,
tri-nationality,

01:09:01.220 --> 01:09:03.800
poly-nationality
within one state

01:09:03.800 --> 01:09:06.760
were options in the '40s that
people we're talking about

01:09:06.760 --> 01:09:08.120
and just got closed down.

01:09:08.120 --> 01:09:11.040
I think it's time to have
those conversations again.

01:09:11.040 --> 01:09:11.540
- Terrific.

01:09:11.540 --> 01:09:12.620
Well, thank you so much.

01:09:12.620 --> 01:09:16.340
I think a measure of a good
